{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Legislate for the repair of potholes within a time frame in the UK.",
        "additional_details": "We pay significant taxes for road use and fuel duty. In 2023\u201324, the Government raised \u00a332\u202fbillion from road-related taxes. Motorists also maintain roadworthy vehicles via MOTs yet face extra damage costs from poorly maintained roads. We believe it is time for road maintenance to become a national priority for the public\u2019s wellbeing. Funding needs to be ring-fenced so that we have a well-maintained road network to reflect the UK\u2019s commitment to a more sustainable society that supports economic growth. ",
        "background": "Set legislation for National Highways and local councils to repair and make safe every pothole found on roads, dual carriageways and motorways, within a specific time frame. This should link to a transparent public national reporting system to track progress and accountability.  ",
